[normal] and a little later on we started paying people for emergency admissions. For every extra emergency admission, you got an extra payment. We had a very rapid growth in emergency admissions. We were paying for every extra one and you had the target. Over a period of time, six or seven years, it grew about 7% a year. 
[normal]We could not afford for it to continue to be growing at that rate, so in about 2010
[normal]&#x2011;
[normal]11 
